Random Password Generator:
This Python project generates a secure random password based on the length specified by the user. It uses Python's built-in random and string modules to create passwords containing uppercase letters, lowercase letters, and numbers.

Features:
User-defined password length
Random combination of letters and digits
Easy-to-use command-line interface

Technologies Used:
Python
random module
string module

Learning Outcomes:
Importing and using Python modules
String manipulation
Loops and user input handling
Basic cybersecurity concepts through password generation
